oc:kn_1456dae9 a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When running conversion multiple times" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Re-encoding the same file with the same settings should produce identical output, but CRF encoding is not perfectly deterministic across versions. Stream copy (-c copy) is deterministic." ;
    oc:hasRationale "CRF uses rate control that may vary slightly; stream copy is a byte-for-byte copy." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_6ca78022 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When encoding H.264 video with libx264" ;
    oc:directiveContent "CRF 18-23 is the recommended quality range for H.264 encoding. Lower values = better quality but larger files. 23 is the default." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This range provides a good balance of visual quality and file size for most use cases." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_82104c14 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting to a container with codec incompatibilities" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not use -c copy when the target container does not support the source codec (e.g., copying H.265 into AVI). This will fail or produce a broken file." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Container formats have specific codec support; mismatched streams cause errors." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_91b7d647 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When file size constraints require precise bitrate targeting" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For best quality at a target bitrate, use two-pass encoding: pass 1 analyzes the video, pass 2 optimizes bit allocation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Single-pass CRF is simpler but two-pass gives more predictable file sizes with optimal quality distribution." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_9b86042c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When choosing encoding speed presets for libx264/libx265" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Preset controls encoding speed vs compression efficiency: ultrafast = fast encode, large file; veryslow = slow encode, small file. 'fast' or 'medium' are good defaults." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Presets trade compute time for compression efficiency, not quality (CRF controls quality)." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_a2fedff1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting to AV1 codec" ;
    oc:directiveContent "AV1 encoding (libaom-av1) is extremely slow compared to H.264/H.265. Expect 10-100x longer encode times." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AV1's complexity gives better compression but at very high computational cost." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_b32452ab a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting between formats that support the same codecs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use -c copy when only changing the container format (e.g., MP4→MKV). This avoids re-encoding, preserves quality, and is near-instant." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Re-encoding degrades quality and takes significant time; stream copying is lossless and fast." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

